WEBVTT

01:02.312 --> 01:05.857
The National Rifle Association
has produced a film

01:05.941 --> 01:08.192
which you are sure to find
of great interest.

01:08.277 --> 01:09.485
Let's look at it.

01:11.822 --> 01:15.408
It was the morning of April 20, 1999,

01:15.492 --> 01:18.745
and it was pretty much
like any other morning in America.

01:19.580 --> 01:21.622
The farmer did his chores.

01:23.041 --> 01:25.793
The milkman made his deliveries.

01:25.878 --> 01:30.089
The president bombed another country
whose name we couldn't pronounce.

01:30.799 --> 01:35.470
Out in Fargo, North Dakota,
Kerry McWilliams went on his morning walk.

01:35.554 --> 01:40.016
Back in Michigan, Mrs. Hughes welcomed
her students for another day of school.

01:41.602 --> 01:46.856
And out in a little town in Colorado,
two boys went bowling at 6:00 in the morning.

01:46.940 --> 01:51.861
Yes, it was a typical day
in the United States of America.

01:56.909 --> 01:57.950
May I help you?

01:58.035 --> 02:00.036
Yeah. I'm here to open up an account.

02:00.120 --> 02:02.663
Okay. What type account would you like?

02:02.748 --> 02:05.208
I want the account
where I can get the free gun.

02:05.292 --> 02:06.459
Okay.

02:06.543 --> 02:09.211
I had spotted an ad
in the local Michigan paper

02:09.295 --> 02:12.465
that said if you opened an account
at North Country Bank,

02:12.549 --> 02:14.133
the bank would give you a gun.

02:14.218 --> 02:16.219
You do a CD and we'll hand you a gun.

02:16.303 --> 02:19.472
We have a whole brochure here
that you can look at.

02:19.556 --> 02:22.934
Once we do the background check
and everything, it's yours to go.

02:23.018 --> 02:26.854
Okay. Um, all right.
Well, that's the account I'd like to open.

02:26.939 --> 02:31.818
We have a vault which at all times
we keep at least 500 firearms.

02:31.902 --> 02:33.569
500 of these you have in your vault?

02:33.654 --> 02:35.112
-In our vault.
-Wow.

02:35.197 --> 02:37.949
-We have to do a background check.
-At the bank here, or...?

02:38.033 --> 02:40.660
At the bank, which,
we are a licensed firearm dealer.

02:40.744 --> 02:43.204
You are? You're a bank
and a licensed firearm dealer.

02:43.288 --> 02:46.415
What do I put for race?
White or Caucasian or...?

02:46.500 --> 02:48.251
-Caucasian.
-Caucasian.

02:48.335 --> 02:53.297
I knew you were gonna make me
spell the – Cau-ca-sian.

02:53.382 --> 02:54.507
-Is that right?
-Yes.

02:54.591 --> 02:55.925
Thank you s –

02:56.009 --> 02:58.302
I don't think that's the part
they're gonna be worried about.

02:58.387 --> 03:01.889
Um, "Have you ever been
adjudicated mentally defective,

03:01.974 --> 03:04.642
or have you ever been committed
to a mental institution?"

03:04.726 --> 03:06.644
I've never been committed
to a mental institution.

03:06.728 --> 03:09.814
What does that mean, "Have I ever been
adjudicated mentally defective"?

03:09.898 --> 03:12.233
Would be something involved with a crime.

03:12.317 --> 03:15.820
With a crime. Okay. So if I'm just normally
mentally defective, but not criminal –

03:15.904 --> 03:16.821
Exactly.

03:16.905 --> 03:20.241
-There you go, Mike.
-Okay. Thank you very much. Wow.

03:20.325 --> 03:22.451
-I have one personally.
-That's a nice action.

03:22.536 --> 03:24.078
-It is. And it's –
-You got one?

03:24.162 --> 03:26.581
It's a straight shooter, let me tell you.

03:29.459 --> 03:31.502
Wow. Sweet.

03:31.587 --> 03:33.004
Well, here's my first question.

03:33.088 --> 03:35.506
Do you think it's a little dangerous
handing out guns in a bank?

