07:53.598 --> 07:55.975
And you a dead man!

07:56.059 --> 07:58.435
You better hope
I can't get no bullets on layaway."

08:01.523 --> 08:04.567
Not far from where
Charlton Heston and I grew up

08:04.651 --> 08:07.987
is a training ground
for the Michigan Militia.

08:08.071 --> 08:09.488
Why do you use the bowling pins?

08:09.573 --> 08:14.076
From a self-defense
or technical standpoint, it's a small target

08:14.161 --> 08:16.996
which also represents the vitals
on a – on a –

08:17.080 --> 08:19.373
on a human being,
should you ever have to shoot at one.

08:21.585 --> 08:24.336
The Michigan Militia
became known around the world

08:24.421 --> 08:27.798
when, on April 19, 1995,

08:27.883 --> 08:31.218
two guys living in Michigan
who had attended militia meetings,

08:31.303 --> 08:33.971
Timothy McVeigh and Terry Nichols,

08:34.054 --> 08:36.849
blew up the federal building
in Oklahoma City,

08:36.933 --> 08:39.351
killing 168 people.

08:40.145 --> 08:45.733
The Michigan Militia wanted everyone to know
that they were nothing like McVeigh and Nichols.

08:45.817 --> 08:47.443
This is an American tradition.

08:47.527 --> 08:50.112
It's an American responsibility to be armed.

08:50.197 --> 08:52.781
If you're not armed,
you're not responsible.

08:52.866 --> 08:56.368
Who's gonna defend your kids?
The cops? The federal government?

08:57.204 --> 08:58.495
No. None of them.

08:58.580 --> 09:01.165
It's your job to defend you and yours.

09:01.249 --> 09:05.002
If you don't do it,
you're in dereliction of duty as an American.

09:05.086 --> 09:06.086
Period.

09:06.171 --> 09:08.756
We're just here to let them know
that, hey, we're here to help.

09:08.840 --> 09:10.758
We're not the bogeymen
that we're made out to be.

09:10.842 --> 09:12.760
We're here to help and defend
the people of this country.

09:12.844 --> 09:16.639
I'm sure you guys are the kind of people
people would like to have as their neighbor.

09:16.723 --> 09:19.016
If somebody's in need,
you're there to help them.

09:19.100 --> 09:22.603
Pretty much. We're all normal people.
We all have regular jobs, professions.

09:22.687 --> 09:25.105
-And this is what we do on our own time.
-What kind of job do you have?

09:25.190 --> 09:27.107
-I'm a draftsman.
-Draftsman? How about you?

09:27.192 --> 09:28.943
-Unemployed right now.
-Unemployed?

09:29.027 --> 09:31.445
-Frank, what do you do for a living?
-I work for a heat-treating company.

09:31.529 --> 09:33.572
- I drive truck for them.
--huh.

09:33.657 --> 09:36.617
-How about you?
-I'm a real estate negotiator.

09:39.788 --> 09:41.455
White collar all the way.

09:42.332 --> 09:45.376
You don't bring that with you, though, do ya,
